properties.Name: StateInsuranceProductTypeCoverageRequirement
properties.Description: The state insurance product type coverage requirement.

Columns.Name: StateRegulatorId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a State Regulator.

Columns.Name: ProductTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product Type.

Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Coverage Type.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period start date that the associated state insurance coverage classification is defined.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period start date that the associated state insurance coverage classification is defined.

Columns.Name: MinimumCoverageLimitAmount
Columns.Description: Minimum Limits of Liability: The least amount of liability coverage that can be purchased, which is generally equivalent to the minimum amount required by state law. In determining rates, a carrier will use the basic limits to develop the base rates. If an insured person wants higher limits, the carrier applies an increased limits factor to the base rate in calculating the new premium for the increased coverage.

Columns.Name: StateInsuranceCoverageStatement
Columns.Description: A statement regarding the state insurance coverage requirement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceRequirementTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Insurance Requirement Type.
